### Example Exam (not the real thing)
* Build an application that manages a list of widgets
* Each widget contains a, b, c (To Be Determined)
* Create a database table to hold widgets
* Create main view that lists the existing widgets
* Create another view to add one widget using a form
* Make sure that both pages produce valid HTML
* Make the page look nice by using header and footer code with a stylesheet



## Apache Web Server
* Apache is the most common web server
* PHP preprocessor is built in


### Setup on Home Computer
* Download from http://sourceforge.net/projects/xampp/files
* Use Murach PHP/MySQL - Appendix A


### Configure Apache
* Edit the config file  c:\\xampp\\php\\php.ini
* Search for "timezone"
    * date.timezone=America/Denver
    
    
### Configure phpMyAdmin
* Edit c:\\xampp\\phpMyAdmin\\config.inc.php
* Authentication Settings

```
$cfg['blowfish_secret'] = '-- My Secret Key -- My Secret Key --'; 
$cfg['Servers'][$i]['auth_type'] = 'cookie';
$cfg['Servers'][$i]['user'] = '';
$cfg['Servers'][$i]['password'] = '';
```


### Server Start Up
* Start Menu XAMPP Control Panel
* Apache Start
* Visit [http://localhost](http://localhost)
* MySQL Start
* Visit [http://localhost/phpmyadmin](http://localhost/phpmyadmin)


### Move Web Documents
* Edit C:\\xampp\\properties.ini

```
apache_htdocs_directory=C:\\Users\\mark.seaman\\Documents\\Documents-2018\\guide\\PhpApps\\web-root
```


